cardDescription.clientTypeDesc:
Summary of common categories of meeting clients that are used in an organisation.
Cisco Webex Desktop : Windows, macOS, web bowser
Cisco Webex Mobile : iPhone, Android, iPad.
Cisco Webex Devices : Cisco room device, Cisco Webex Board.
Others: Any unknown endpoints or clients that don’t fit the other categories.
cardDescription.totalCallsDesc:
Cloud Calls: Number of calls that could not utilise enterprise Video Mesh Nodes, because of no connection to the enterprise network or being subject to enforced policy.
Overflowed to Cloud: Number of calls made within an enterprise but overflowed to a cloud cluster.
On-Premises: Number of calls hosted on any of the enterprise clusters.
cardDescription.totalCallsClusterDesc:
Redirected by this Cluster: Number of calls that could not be hosted by this cluster and hence were redirected.
On-Premises: Number of calls hosted on any of the enterprise clusters.
cardDescription.meetsHostTypeDesc:
Summary of meetings based on where the organisation’s calls were hosted.
On Premises: Meeting and participants were hosted on the enterprise clusters
Cloud: Meeting and participants were hosted on cloud clusters
Cloud and On-Premises: Meeting and participants cascaded between enterprise and cloud clusters
cardDescription.redirect: Number of calls that could not be hosted by this cluster, and hence were redirected.
cardDescription.overflow: Number of calls that were made within an enterprise but overflowed to a cloud cluster
cardDescription.clusterInServiceDesc: Percentage of clusters that can host calls in the organisation.

graphDescription.utilizationOrgDesc: Average utilisation trend for all clusters in an organisation
graphDescription.utilizationClusterDesc: Average utilisation trend for the selected cluster in an organisation, compared to the average utilisation for all the clusters
graphDescription.callActivityDesc: Provides a view of the call activity trend across the organisation, showing the calls that were hosted on-premises and calls hosted on the cloud. The calls that overflowed to the cloud are represented as dots on the cloud call graph. Hover over a dot to show the number of calls that overflowed to the cloud at that instance.
graphDescription.calldistributionOrgDesc: Provides a view of how calls are distributed across the different on-premise clusters in the organisation. This information helps an admin plan an organisation’s cluster capacity. Calls that cannot be hosted on a specific on-premises cluster are redirected to another on-premises cluster. These redirects are represented as dots on the graph. Hover over a dot to show the number of calls that were redirected from that specific cluster.
graphDescription.calldistributionClusterDesc: Provides a view of the call activity trend on a specific cluster. This information helps an admin to plan an organisation’s cluster capacity. Calls that cannot be hosted on this specific cluster are redirected to another on-premises cluster. These redirects are represented as dots on the graph. Hover over a dot to show the number of calls redirected from this specific cluster at that instance.
graphDescription.clusterInServiceOrgDesc:
Number of clusters that were in service to host calls over the selected time period. Click any of the clusters in the Cluster Availability graph to directly navigate to the Nodes In Service graph.
Green: clusters that have all nodes in service.
Yellow: clusters that have 1 or more nodes that are not in service.
Red: clusters that have no available nodes in service.
Grey: data not available.
